freenet.client.async
Class USKInserter

java.lang.Object
  freenet.client.async.USKInserter
All Implemented Interfaces:
ClientPutState, PutCompletionCallback, USKCallback, USKFetcherCallback
public class USKInserter
extends Object
implements ClientPutState, USKFetcherCallback, PutCompletionCallback

Insert a USK. The algorithm is simply to do a thorough search for the latest edition, and insert at the following slot. Thereafter, if we get a collision, increment our slot; if we get more than 5 consecutive collisions, search for the latest slot again.

onFoundEdition

public void onFoundEdition(long l,
                           USK key,
                           com.db4o.ObjectContainer container,
                           ClientContext context,
                           boolean lastContentWasMetadata,
                           short codec,
                           byte[] hisData,
                           boolean newKnownGood,
                           boolean newSlotToo)
Description copied from interface: USKFetcherCallback
Found the latest edition. **This is terminal for a USKFetcherCallback**. It isn't for a USKCallback subscription.

Specified by:
onFoundEdition in interface USKCallback
Specified by:
onFoundEdition in interface USKFetcherCallback
Parameters:
l - The edition number.
key - The key.
newKnownGood - If the highest known good edition (which has actually been fetched with what it pointed to) has increased. Otherwise, the highest known SSK slot has been increased, from which searches will start, but we do not know whether it can actually be fetched successfully.
newSlotToo - If newKnownGood is set, this indicates whether it is also a new highest known SSK slot. If newKnownGood is not set, there is always a new highest known SSK slot.
